author: @xtheory9640
text: cd   for changing directory. ls   for showing a list of all the files in the directory. ls -la for showing the list of files in list format + showing all the hidden files. mkdir  for making a new directory. touch  for creating a new file. cp   for copying a file. cp -r  for copy a directory. mv  for renaming and / or moving a file. open  for opening a file. rm   for removing a file. rm -rf  for force removing a directory. man (-r)  this will show some information about -r. -r is an example.
